{"name": "opentelemetry-instrumentation-watsonx", "metadata": {"name": "opentelemetry-instrumentation-watsonx", "version": "0.33.12", "classifiers": ["License :: OSI Approved :: Apache Software License", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.10", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.11", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.12", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.13", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.9"], "home_page": "https://github.com/traceloop/openllmetry/tree/main/packages/opentelemetry-instrumentation-watsonx", "license": "Apache-2.0", "documentation_url": null, "dependencies": ["opentelemetry-api", "opentelemetry-instrumentation", "opentelemetry-semantic-conventions", "opentelemetry-semantic-conventions-ai"], "summary": "OpenTelemetry IBM Watsonx Instrumentation", "upload_time": 1731529666}, "documentation": ["# OpenTelemetry IBM Watsonx Instrumentation\n\nThis library allows tracing IBM Watsonx prompts and completions sent with the official [IBM Watson Machine Learning library](https://ibm.github.io/watson-machine-learning-sdk/) and [IBM watsonx.ai library](https://ibm.github.io/watsonx-ai-python-sdk/).\n\n## Installation\n\n```bash\npip install opentelemetry-instrumentation-watsonx\n```\n\n## Example usage\n\n```python\nfrom opentelemetry.instrumentation.watsonx import WatsonxInstrumentor\n\nWatsonxInstrumentor().instrument()\n```\n\n## Privacy\n\n**By default, this instrumentation logs prompts, completions, and embeddings to span attributes**. This gives you a clear visibility into how your LLM application is working, and can make it easy to debug and evaluate the quality of the outputs.\n\nHowever, you may want to disable this logging for privacy reasons, as they may contain highly sensitive data from your users. You may also simply want to reduce the size of your traces.\n\nTo disable logging, set the `TRACELOOP_TRACE_CONTENT` environment variable to `false`.\n\n```bash\nTRACELOOP_TRACE_CONTENT=false\n```\n\n## SSL Issue\n\nIn case of SSL handshake issues (or similar ones) as follows:\n\n```\nE0423 17:04:25.197068000 6150713344 ssl_transport_security.cc:1420]    Handshake failed with fatal error SSL_ERROR_SSL: error:100000f7:SSL routines:OPENSSL_internal:WRONG_VERSION_NUMBER.\n```\n\nYou can instruct the exporter with an environment variable to ignore SSL errors:\n\n```bash\nOTEL_EXPORTER_OTLP_INSECURE=true\n```\n\n"], "modules": [{"name": "opentelemetry.instrumentation.watsonx.utils", "documentation": [], "functions": [{"name": "opentelemetry.instrumentation.watsonx.utils.dont_throw", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "func", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["A decorator that wraps the passed in function and logs exceptions instead of throwing them.\n\n@param func: The function to wrap\n@return: The wrapper function"]}], "variables": [], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "opentelemetry.instrumentation.watsonx.version", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [{"name": "opentelemetry.instrumentation.watsonx.version.__version__", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "opentelemetry.instrumentation.watsonx.config", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [{"name": "opentelemetry.instrumentation.watsonx.config.Config", "bases": [], "methods": [], "class_variables": [{"name": "opentelemetry.instrumentation.watsonx.config.Config.exception_logger", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": []}], "exports": []}, {"name": "opentelemetry.instrumentation.watsonx", "documentation": ["OpenTelemetry IBM Watsonx AI instrumentation"], "functions": [{"name": "opentelemetry.instrumentation.watsonx._set_span_attribute", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "span", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "name", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "value", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns